\hline \theta & V' & V'' & Meaning \\ \hline 0 & 0 & 2\kexp & Minima \\ \hline \cos^{-1} \frac{1}{\sqrt{3}} & 0 & -\frac{2\sqrt{2}}{\sqrt{3}}\kexp & Maxima \\ \hline \end{tabular} \end{align} %text Hence, $V$ is maximum when $\theta = \cos^{-1} \frac{1}{\sqrt{3}}$ \incorrect % \begin{align} \begin{tabular}{NNNc}
\hline \theta & V' & V'' & Meaning \\ \hline 0 & 0 & \kexp & Minima \\ \hline \cos^{-1} \frac{1}{\sqrt{3}} & 0 & -\frac{2}{3}\kexp & Maxima \\ \hline \end{tabular} \end{align} %text Hence, $V$ is maximum when $\theta = \cos^{-1} \frac{1}{\sqrt{3}}$%

